hook.real_world_problem:
Your payment service has grown. Configuration is scattered across many classes:

```java
// PaymentService.java:
@Value("${payment.gateway.url}")      String url;
@Value("${payment.gateway.timeout}")  int timeoutMs;
@Value("${payment.gateway.retries}")  int retries;
@Value("${payment.gateway.api-key}")  String apiKey;

// NotificationService.java:
@Value("${notification.email.host}")  String emailHost;
@Value("${notification.email.port}")  int emailPort;
@Value("${notification.sms.url}")     String smsUrl;
@Value("${notification.sms.token}")   String smsToken;

// DatabaseConfig.java:
@Value("${db.pool.min-size}")  int minPoolSize;
@Value("${db.pool.max-size}")  int maxPoolSize;
// ... 20 more @Value fields
```

Problems: no IDE autocomplete, no type-safe binding, no validation, scattered.

**With @ConfigurationProperties:**
```java
@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "payment.gateway")
public record PaymentGatewayProps(
    String url,
    Duration timeout,
    int retries,
    String apiKey
) {}

@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "notification.email")
public record EmailProps(
    String host,
    int port,
    String from
) {}
```

```properties
# Grouped, readable, IDE-autocomplete:
payment.gateway.url=https://api.razorpay.com
payment.gateway.timeout=5s
payment.gateway.retries=3
payment.gateway.api-key=${RAZORPAY_KEY}

notification.email.host=smtp.gmail.com
notification.email.port=587
```

And environment differences via profiles:
```
application-dev.properties  → local URLs, H2 DB, DEBUG logging
application-prod.properties → real URLs, PostgreSQL, WARN logging
```

One codebase, many environments. Zero conditional logic.

concept_explanation.config_properties_basics:
**@ConfigurationProperties — type-safe property binding:**

```java
// application.properties:
// payment.gateway.url=https://api.razorpay.com
// payment.gateway.timeout=5000
// payment.gateway.max-retries=3
// payment.gateway.api-key=rzp_test_abc123

// Java record bound to these properties:
@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "payment.gateway")
public record PaymentGatewayProps(
    String url,          // payment.gateway.url
    int timeout,         // payment.gateway.timeout
    int maxRetries,      // payment.gateway.max-retries (kebab-case → camelCase)
    String apiKey        // payment.gateway.api-key
) {}
```

**Enabling: two ways:**
```java
// Option 1: @EnableConfigurationProperties on any @Configuration:
@SpringBootApplication
@EnableConfigurationProperties(PaymentGatewayProps.class)
public class Application { ... }

// Option 2: @ConfigurationPropertiesScan (scans for all in package):
@SpringBootApplication
@ConfigurationPropertiesScan
public class Application { ... }
```

**Inject and use:**
```java
@Service
public class PaymentService {
    private final PaymentGatewayProps props;

    PaymentService(PaymentGatewayProps props) { this.props = props; }

    public void process(Payment payment) {
        // Clean, typed access:
        HttpClient.post(props.url())
            .timeout(Duration.ofMillis(props.timeout()))
            .retry(props.maxRetries())
            .header("x-api-key", props.apiKey());
    }
}
```

concept_explanation.validation:
**Validate configuration at startup with @Validated:**

```java
import jakarta.validation.constraints.*;
import org.springframework.validation.annotation.Validated;

@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "payment.gateway")
@Validated  // triggers Bean Validation on startup
public record PaymentGatewayProps(
    @NotBlank(message = "payment.gateway.url is required")
    @Pattern(regexp = "https://.*", message = "URL must use HTTPS")
    String url,

    @Min(value = 1000, message = "timeout must be at least 1000ms")
    @Max(value = 30000, message = "timeout cannot exceed 30 seconds")
    int timeout,

    @Min(1) @Max(10)
    int maxRetries,

    @NotBlank(message = "API key is required — set PAYMENT_API_KEY env var")
    String apiKey
) {}
```

If any constraint fails at startup:
```
Application context failed to start:
Configuration property 'payment.gateway.url' must use HTTPS
```

Fail-fast: bad configuration is caught at startup, not at runtime.

concept_explanation.nested_properties:
**Nested @ConfigurationProperties:**

```java
// Nested record for related sub-groups:
@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "notification")
public record NotificationProps(
    Email email,
    Sms sms,
    boolean enabled
) {
    public record Email(
        String host,
        int port,
        String from,
        boolean tls
    ) {}

    public record Sms(
        String url,
        String apiKey,
        int rateLimit
    ) {}
}

// application.properties:
// notification.enabled=true
// notification.email.host=smtp.gmail.com
// notification.email.port=587
// notification.email.from=noreply@codequest.in
// notification.email.tls=true
// notification.sms.url=https://api.sms.in
// notification.sms.api-key=${SMS_API_KEY}
// notification.sms.rate-limit=100

// Injection:
@Service class NotificationService {
    private final NotificationProps props;
    NotificationService(NotificationProps p) { props = p; }
    void sendEmail(String to, String body) {
        if (!props.enabled()) return;
        mailer.send(props.email().host(), props.email().port(), to, body);
    }
}
```

concept_explanation.spring_profiles:
**Spring Profiles — environment-specific configuration:**

```
src/main/resources/
  application.properties          ← shared (always loaded)
  application-dev.properties      ← dev overrides
  application-staging.properties  ← staging overrides
  application-prod.properties     ← production overrides
```

```properties
# application.properties (shared):
spring.application.name=payment-service
server.port=8080
logging.pattern.console=%d{HH:mm:ss} [%thread] %-5level %msg%n

# application-dev.properties:
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:devdb
spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop
spring.jpa.show-sql=true
logging.level.root=DEBUG
payment.gateway.url=https://sandbox.razorpay.com
payment.gateway.api-key=rzp_test_abc123

# application-prod.properties:
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:postgresql://prod-db:5432/payments
spring.datasource.username=${DB_USER}
spring.datasource.password=${DB_PASSWORD}
spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=validate
logging.level.root=WARN
payment.gateway.url=https://api.razorpay.com
payment.gateway.api-key=${RAZORPAY_KEY}
```

**Activating profiles:**
```properties
# In application.properties:
spring.profiles.active=dev

# Via command line:
java -jar app.jar --spring.profiles.active=prod

# Via environment variable:
SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE=prod java -jar app.jar

# In @SpringBootTest:
@SpringBootTest
@ActiveProfiles("dev")
class MyTest { ... }
```

**@Profile on beans:**
```java
// Only instantiated when 'dev' profile is active:
@Component @Profile("dev")
public class DevDataSeeder implements CommandLineRunner {
    @Override public void run(String... args) {
        System.out.println("[DEV] Seeding test data...");
        repo.save(new Product("Test Mouse", 1, "Electronics"));
    }
}

// Only in prod:
@Service @Profile("prod")
public class RealEmailService implements EmailService {
    // Uses real SMTP — don't call in dev/test
}

// In dev/test:
@Service @Profile({"dev", "test"})
public class MockEmailService implements EmailService {
    @Override public void send(String to, String body) {
        System.out.println("[MOCK EMAIL] To: " + to + " Body: " + body);
    }
}
```

